VALUES
(43, 6, 43, 43, 6, 64, 64, 'Murmur not among yourselves', 'Belief and Unbelief in Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief and unbelief among Jesus'' followers. In both passages, the murmuring indicates doubt, while the mention of those who believe not emphasizes the division in faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 43, 40, 16, 8, 8, NULL, 'Murmuring and Reasoning Among Themselves', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of individuals murmuring or reasoning among themselves, reflecting a lack of understanding or faith. Jesus addresses their internal discussions, highlighting their doubts in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 43, 41, 9, 33, 33, 'murmur not among yourselves', 'Disputes Among Themselves', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of internal disputes among Jesus'' followers. In John, Jesus addresses murmuring, while in Mark, He questions them about their disputes, highlighting a common concern of misunderstanding or disagreement.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 43, 43, 16, 19, 19, 'murmur not among yourselves', 'Inquiry Among Themselves', 'Both passages emphasize the act of questioning among the disciples. In John 6:43, Jesus addresses their murmuring, while in John 16:19, he acknowledges their desire to ask about his words, indicating a shared theme of internal dialogue and confusion.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 44, 43, 6, 65, 65, 'except the Father which hath sent me draw him', 'Divine Drawing to Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize that no one can come to Jesus unless it is given by the Father. This connection highlights the necessity of divine initiative in the process of coming to Christ.', 'theme', 0.7969999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 44, 43, 6, 39, 40, 'I will raise him up at the last day', 'Connection of Resurrection Promises', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of resurrection ''at the last day.'' They highlight the role of the Father in drawing believers to the Son, ensuring that none are lost.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 44, 40, 11, 25, 27, 'the Father which hath sent me draw him', 'Divine Revelation and Drawing', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Father in revealing truth and drawing individuals to the Son. John 6:44 highlights that no one can come to Jesus unless drawn by the Father, while Matthew 11:25-27 discusses how the Father reveals truths to the humble. This connection highlights the divine initiative in understanding and relationship.', 'theme', 0.552, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 44, 49, 2, 4, 10, 'the Father which hath sent me draw him', 'Divine Drawing and Grace', 'This connection highlights the role of God in salvation, as both passages emphasize that it is through God''s initiative and grace that individuals are drawn to Christ and saved. John 6:44 speaks of the Father drawing people, while Ephesians 2:4-10 elaborates on being saved by grace through faith.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 44, 40, 16, 17, 17, NULL, 'Divine Revelation and Drawing', 'This connection highlights the role of the Father in revealing truth and drawing individuals to Jesus. Both passages emphasize that divine action is necessary for understanding and coming to faith.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 44, 56, 3, 3, 5, 'the Father which hath sent me draw him', 'Divine Drawing and Mercy', 'This connection highlights the role of God''s initiative in salvation. John 6:44 emphasizes that the Father draws individuals to Christ, while Titus 3:5 underscores that salvation is not based on human efforts but on God''s mercy.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 44, 24, 31, 3, 3, 'draw him', 'Divine Drawing in Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being drawn by God. In John 6:44, it states that the Father draws individuals to Jesus, while Jeremiah 31:3 expresses God''s lovingkindness in drawing His people to Himself.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 45, 23, 54, 13, 13, 'taught of God', 'Teaching by God', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being taught by God. John 6:45 references being taught of God, while Isaiah 54:13 states that children shall be taught of the Lord.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 45, 24, 31, 33, 34, 'taught of God', 'Teaching and Knowledge of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of being taught by God and knowing Him. Both passages emphasize that all people will have direct knowledge of God, eliminating the need for intermediaries.', 'theme', 0.9159999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 45, 58, 10, 16, 16, 'taught of God', 'Teaching and Covenant Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine instruction. Both passages emphasize that God imparts knowledge and laws directly to individuals, leading them to Him.', 'theme', 0.7549999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 45, 58, 8, 10, 11, 'taught of God', 'Teaching and Knowing God', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine teaching and knowledge of God. Both passages emphasize that all will be taught by God and will know Him directly, eliminating the need for intermediaries.', 'theme', 0.699, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 45, 52, 4, 9, 9, 'taught of God', 'Divine Teaching on Love', 'Both passages emphasize being ''taught of God.'' John highlights that those who learn from the Father come to Him, while Thessalonians affirms that believers are taught by God to love one another. This connection highlights the theme of divine instruction in the lives of believers.', 'theme', 0.671, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 45, 33, 4, 2, 2, 'taught of God', 'Teaching of God Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being taught by God. John 6:45 references individuals who have learned from the Father, while Micah 4:2 speaks of nations coming to be taught His ways.', 'theme', 0.538, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 45, 23, 2, 3, 3, 'taught of God', 'Divine Teaching Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being taught by God. Both passages emphasize that individuals who learn from God will seek Him and follow His ways.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 46, 43, 1, 18, 18, NULL, 'Seeing God and Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize that no man has seen God, highlighting the unique role of the Son in revealing the Father. This connection underscores the exclusivity of the Son''s experience of the Father.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 46, 43, 7, 29, 29, 'he hath seen the Father', 'Connection of Divine Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the relationship between knowing God and being sent by Him. In both passages, the emphasis is on the unique knowledge of the Father and the authority of Jesus as the one sent from Him.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 46, 40, 11, 27, 27, 'save he which is of God', 'Knowledge of the Father and Son', 'Both passages emphasize that no one knows the Father except the Son, and vice versa. This connection highlights the unique relationship between the Father and the Son, as well as the exclusivity of their knowledge.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 46, 42, 10, 22, 22, NULL, 'Knowledge of the Father and Son', 'Both passages emphasize the unique relationship between the Father and the Son. John 6:46 states that only those of God have seen the Father, while Luke 10:22 highlights that only the Son knows the Father, indicating a deep, exclusive knowledge shared between them.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 46, 54, 6, 16, 16, NULL, 'Visibility of the Father', 'Both passages emphasize that no man has seen the Father, highlighting the divine nature and inaccessibility of God. This connection underscores the unique relationship of Jesus with the Father as the one who has seen Him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 46, 51, 1, 15, 15, 'seen the Father', 'Connection of Divine Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeing God. John 6:46 states that only those of God have seen the Father, while Colossians 1:15 describes Christ as the image of the invisible God, suggesting that Jesus reveals the Father to humanity.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 46, 62, 4, 12, 12, NULL, 'Seeing God and Love', 'Both passages emphasize that ''no man hath seen God'' and highlight the importance of love among believers. This connection illustrates the idea that while God remains unseen, His presence is manifested through love in the community.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 47, 43, 3, 36, 36, 'everlasting life', 'Connection of Everlasting Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''everlasting life'' as a result of belief in Jesus. They highlight the importance of faith in the Son for receiving eternal life and the consequences of unbelief.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 47, 51, 3, 3, 4, 'everlasting life', 'Connection of Life in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of everlasting life through belief in Christ. John 6:47 states that belief leads to everlasting life, while Colossians 3:3-4 speaks of life being hidden with Christ, culminating in glory.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 47, 43, 3, 16, 16, 'hath everlasting life', 'Connection of Everlasting Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of everlasting life for those who believe. They highlight the importance of belief in Jesus as the pathway to eternal life.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 47, 45, 5, 9, 10, 'everlasting life', 'Connection of Salvation and Life', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation through belief and reconciliation. John 6:47 speaks of everlasting life for believers, while Romans 5:9-10 discusses being saved by Christ''s life after reconciliation.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 47, 62, 5, 12, 13, 'He that believeth on me hath everlasting life', 'Eternal Life Through Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of belief in the Son for obtaining eternal life. John 6:47 states that belief in Jesus grants everlasting life, while 1 John 5:12-13 reinforces that having the Son equates to having life.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
